# ARTEMIS — CURSOR PROJECT RULES
# These rules apply to every file, every feature, every prompt in this project.
# Read this fully before responding to any request.

## WHAT THIS PROJECT IS

Artemis is an apparel supply chain intelligence and execution platform.
Four planes every piece of code must serve:

  PLANE A — INTELLIGENCE    reads market data, surfaces signals
  PLANE B — EXECUTION       acts on signals, facilitates transactions
  PLANE C — NETWORK         connects importers and manufacturers
  PLANE D — REVENUE         logs every monetisation event

## THE MASTER SCHEMA IS THE CONTRACT

Every model, endpoint, and function must match docs/MASTER_SCHEMA.md exactly.
Do not invent tables. Do not invent fields. Do not change field types.
If a feature needs a field not in the schema, STOP and flag it. Never add silently.

## DATABASE

- SQLite via SQLAlchemy 2.0
- File: artemis.db at project root
- All models in: database/models/
- Every model must have created_at and updated_at
- PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON on every connection
- Never use raw SQL strings. SQLAlchemy ORM only.

## THE CENTRAL ENTITY IS PROGRAM

Every intelligence output, execution action, and revenue event is scoped
to a PROGRAM. Program links one IMPORTER to one CMT_FACTORY for one
PRODUCT_SPECIFICATION. Never create orphaned records.

## THE FOUR EXECUTION FLOWS

1. COMMODITY HEDGING (Pillar HQ)
   Trigger: cotton.contango_signal > 5.0 AND program.commodity_hedge_status = UNHEDGED
   Creates: hedge_opportunity record
   Executes: POST /pillar/quote then POST /pillar/execute
   Creates: hedge_portfolio record
   Updates: program.commodity_hedge_status = HEDGED
   Logs: revenue_transaction type hedge_share
   Feeds back: forward_landed_cost_90day updated with locked price

2. OCEAN FREIGHT REVERSE AUCTION (Carrier Network)
   Trigger: ship_date within 45 days AND freight_booking_id IS NULL
   Creates: ocean_freight_rfq auto-populated from program
   Broadcasts: to carrier API network
   Receives: carrier_bid records
   Awards: rfq.status = AWARDED, award_timestamp set
   Logs: revenue_transaction type freight_booking

3. CUSTOMS CLEARANCE (Customs Broker Partner)
   Trigger: program.status = SHIPPED AND customs_clearance_id IS NULL
   Creates: customs_clearance_filing auto-populated from program
   Updates: duty_amount_paid feeds back to program.landed_cost_actual
   Logs: revenue_transaction type customs_referral

4. SUPPLY CHAIN FINANCE (SCF Provider)
   Trigger: program.status = COMMITTED AND factory financing_rate > 10.0
   Creates: supply_chain_finance_offer
   Logs: revenue_transaction type scf_spread ON DISBURSEMENT ONLY

## 15 INTELLIGENCE OUTPUT TABLES

current_landed_cost_per_dozen
forward_landed_cost_90day
most_cost_effective_corridor
commodity_risk_in_open_programs
hedge_opportunity_recommendation
top5_competitor_sourcing
retailer_demand_forecast
tariff_exposure_analysis
factory_financing_impact
factory_capacity_constraints
otd_risk_score_per_program
freight_booking_window
scf_opportunity_per_factory
competitor_factory_intel
program_pnl_with_levers

Every output must include as_of_date and model_version.
Every output must also write a prediction_log record.

## DATA QUALITY RULES

Cotton:        stale if as_of_date older than 2 days
FX rates:      stale if as_of_date older than 2 days
Crude oil:     warn above 5 days, error above 7 days
Ocean freight: stale above 8 days
Yarn:          confidence_score 0.68 currently (priors only, no real data yet)

## FOB FORMULA

FOB = fabric_cost_doz + cmt_cost_doz + trim_cost_doz + overhead_doz + financing_cost_doz
financing_cost_doz = (fob_approx x rate_pct/100) x (payment_days/365)
payment_days: Bangladesh 90, India 90, Vietnam 90, China 60
financing_cost_doz is ALWAYS stored separately. Never rolled into overhead.

## REVENUE TYPES

subscription, hedge_share, freight_booking, drayage_booking,
intermodal_booking, customs_referral, scf_spread, data_licensing

## DATA DISCIPLINE — NON-NEGOTIABLE

Rule 1 — APPEND ONLY:
  Never overwrite existing rows in market data tables.
  Always call mark_latest() before inserting, then insert a new row.
  mark_latest() is in database/base.py.
  Tables that are append-only: cotton, crude_oil, fx_rates,
  commodity_futures, ocean_freight_rates, retailer_financials,
  retailer_intelligence_extract, retailer_signal_evidence,
  labour_cost_by_country, energy_cost, factory_financing_cost, yarn.

Rule 2 — LOG EVERY PULL:
  Every ingestion script must use IngestionContext from
  database/ingestion_context.py.
  No ingestion run completes without a log row in ingestion_log.
  Status must be one of: 'running' | 'success' | 'partial' | 'failed'.

Rule 3 — VALIDATE ON INGESTION:
  Every field that has a validator in database/validation/ingestion_validators.py
  must be passed through validate_and_log() before being stored.
  A validation failure stores NULL rather than bad data.
  Never let a bad value enter the database silently.

Rule 4 — IDEMPOTENCY:
  Before every insert, call is_duplicate_row() from database/base.py.
  If True, call ctx.stale() and skip the insert. Never create duplicate rows.

Rule 5 — REFERENTIAL INTEGRITY:
  Before writing FK rows, call assert_fk_exists() from database/base.py.
  If False, call ctx.rejected() and do not insert.

Rule 6 — SOURCE FINGERPRINTING:
  Every append-only row must populate source, data_source_url, and pulled_at.
  source and data_source_url are NOT NULL on all append-only tables.

Rule 7 — MODEL VERSION:
  All intelligence output rows must have model_version in x.y.z format.
  Use CURRENT_MODEL_VERSION from database/constants.py.

HEALTH CHECK:
  Run python scripts/health_check.py after every ingestion cycle.

OCEAN FREIGHT CONTAINER TYPES:
  20ft standard  — dense/heavy cargo, smaller programs (rate_20ft_usd)
  40ft standard  — primary apparel container (rate_40ft_usd)
  40ft High Cube — bulky cartons and hanger programs (rate_40ft_hc_usd)

## NEVER DO

- No pandas for database work
- No hardcoded corridor strings, use CORRIDORS from constants.py
- No intelligence logic inside API route handlers
- No raw database objects returned from API
- No skipping prediction_log when writing intelligence output
- No landed_cost_actual set before customs duty is confirmed
- No scf revenue logged before disbursement_date is set
- No String type for rates or amounts, always Numeric or Decimal
